<tbody><tr>
<th scope="col">Table element
</th>
<th scope="col">Wikitext
</th>
<th scope="col">Required
</th>
<th scope="col">Usage notes
</th></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table start
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">{|</kbd>
</td>
<td>Required
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table caption
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|+</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Only between table start and first table row.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table row
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|-</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Can be omitted before the first row.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table header cell
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">!</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Consecutive table header cells may be added on same line separated by double marks (<code>!!</code>); or start on new lines, each with its own single mark (<code>!</code>).
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table data cell
</th>
<td><span class="nowrap"><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|</kbd> or <kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">||</kbd></span>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Consecutive table data cells may be added on same line separated by double marks (<code>||</code>) or start on new lines, each with its own single mark (<code>|</code>). This mark is also used to separate <a href="/wiki/HTML_attribute" title="HTML attribute">HTML attributes</a> from cell and caption contents.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table end
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|}</kbd>
</td>
<td>Required
</td>
<td>
</td></tr></tbody></table>, <table class="wikitable">

<tbody><tr>
<th scope="row" style="width: 10%;">Row header
</th>

<tbody><tr>
<td style="background-color: #eaecf0;">
</td>
<th scope="col">XHTML
</th>
<th scope="col">Wiki-pipe
</th></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;table&gt;...&lt;/table&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>{|<br/>...<br/>|}</code>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Caption
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;caption&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">caption</var>&lt;/caption&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>|+ <var style="padding-right: 1px;">caption</var></code>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Header cell
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;th scope="col"&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">column header</var>&lt;/th&gt;</code><br/>
<p><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;th scope="row"&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">row header</var>&lt;/th&gt;</code>
</p>
</td>
<td><code>! scope="col" | <var style="padding-right: 1px;">column header</var></code><br/>
<p><code>! scope="row" | <var style="padding-right: 1px;">row header</var></code>
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Row
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;tr&gt;...&lt;/tr&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>|-</code>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Data cell
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;td&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var>&lt;/td&gt;</code><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;td&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell2</var>&lt;/td&gt;</code><br/><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;td&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell3</var>&lt;/td&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>| <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var> || <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell2</var> || <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell3</var></code><br/>
<p>or<br/>
<code>| <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var></code><br/>
<code>| <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell2</var></code><br/>
<code>| <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell3</var></code>
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Cell attribute
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;td style="font-size: 87%;"&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var>&lt;/td&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>| style="font-size: 87%;" | <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var></code>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Sample table
</th>
<td><div class="mw-highlight mw-highlight-lang-html mw-content-ltr" dir="ltr"><pre><span></span><span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">table</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>1<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>2<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>3<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>4<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">table</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
</pre></div>
</td>
<td><pre>{|
| 1 || 2
|-
| 3 || 4
|}</pre>
<div>

<td>2
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>3</td>
<td>4
</td></tr></tbody></table>
</div>
</td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top;">
<th scope="row">Pros
</th>
<td>
<ul><li>Can preview or debug with any XHTML editor</li>
<li>Can be indented for easier reading</li>
<li>Well-known</li>
<li>Insensitive to newlines</li>
<li>No characters like "|", which can collide with template and parser function syntax</li></ul>
</td>
<td>
<ul><li>Easy to write</li>
<li>Easy to read</li>
<li>Takes little space</li>
<li>Can be learned quickly</li></ul>
</td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top;">
<th scope="row">Cons
</th>
<td>
<ul><li>Tedious</li>
<li>Takes a lot of space</li>
<li>Difficult to read quickly</li>
<li>Debugging more difficult because of tag pairing requirements</li>
<li>Indented code might not match nesting.</li>
<li>Confusing newline behaviour as they only occasionally break cells.</li></ul>
</td>
<td>
<ul><li>Unfamiliar syntax for experienced HTML editors</li>
<li>Rigid structure</li>
<li>Cannot be indented for clarity</li>
<li>HTML tag text may be easier to read than pipes, plus signs, dashes, etc.</li>
<li>Requires using <code>{{<a href="/wiki/Template:!" title="Template:!">!</a>}}</code> to pass a <code> | </code> character in a parameter.</li>
<li>Sensitive to newlines; see <a href="/wiki/Help:Newlines_and_spaces" title="Help:Newlines and spaces">Help:Newlines and spaces</a>.</li></ul>
</td></tr></tbody></table>, <table class="wikitable" style="margin: auto;">
<tbody><tr>
<td>1</td>
<td>2
</td></tr>

<td>3</td>

<tbody><tr>
<th scope="col">Table element
</th>
<th scope="col">Wikitext
</th>
<th scope="col">Required
</th>
<th scope="col">Usage notes
</th></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table start
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">{|</kbd>
</td>
<td>Required
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table caption
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|+</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Only between table start and first table row.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table row
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|-</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Can be omitted before the first row.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table header cell
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">!</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Consecutive table header cells may be added on same line separated by double marks (<code>!!</code>); or start on new lines, each with its own single mark (<code>!</code>).
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table data cell
</th>
<td><span class="nowrap"><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|</kbd> or <kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">||</kbd></span>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Consecutive table data cells may be added on same line separated by double marks (<code>||</code>) or start on new lines, each with its own single mark (<code>|</code>). This mark is also used to separate <a href="/wiki/HTML_attribute" title="HTML attribute">HTML attributes</a> from cell and caption contents.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table end
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|}</kbd>
</td>
<td>Required
</td>
<td>

<tbody><tr>
<td style="background-color: #eaecf0;">
</td>
<th scope="col">XHTML
</th>
<th scope="col">Wiki-pipe
</th></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;table&gt;...&lt;/table&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>{|<br/>...<br/>|}</code>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Caption
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;caption&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">caption</var>&lt;/caption&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>|+ <var style="padding-right: 1px;">caption</var></code>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Header cell
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;th scope="col"&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">column header</var>&lt;/th&gt;</code><br/>
<p><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;th scope="row"&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">row header</var>&lt;/th&gt;</code>
</p>
</td>
<td><code>! scope="col" | <var style="padding-right: 1px;">column header</var></code><br/>
<p><code>! scope="row" | <var style="padding-right: 1px;">row header</var></code>
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Row
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;tr&gt;...&lt;/tr&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>|-</code>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Data cell
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;td&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var>&lt;/td&gt;</code><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;td&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell2</var>&lt;/td&gt;</code><br/><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;td&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell3</var>&lt;/td&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>| <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var> || <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell2</var> || <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell3</var></code><br/>
<p>or<br/>
<code>| <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var></code><br/>
<code>| <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell2</var></code><br/>
<code>| <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell3</var></code>
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Cell attribute
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;td style="font-size: 87%;"&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var>&lt;/td&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>| style="font-size: 87%;" | <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var></code>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Sample table
</th>
<td><div class="mw-highlight mw-highlight-lang-html mw-content-ltr" dir="ltr"><pre><span></span><span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">table</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>1<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>2<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>3<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>4<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">table</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
</pre></div>
</td>
<td><pre>{|
| 1 || 2
|-
| 3 || 4
|}</pre>
<div>
<table class="wikitable" style="margin: auto;">
<tbody><tr>
<td>1</td>
<td>2
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>3</td>
<td>4
</td></tr></tbody></table>
</div>
</td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top;">
<th scope="row">Pros
</th>
<td>
<ul><li>Can preview or debug with any XHTML editor</li>
<li>Can be indented for easier reading</li>
<li>Well-known</li>
<li>Insensitive to newlines</li>
<li>No characters like "|", which can collide with template and parser function syntax</li></ul>
</td>
<td>
<ul><li>Easy to write</li>
<li>Easy to read</li>
<li>Takes little space</li>
<li>Can be learned quickly</li></ul>
</td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top;">
<th scope="row">Cons
</th>
<td>
<ul><li>Tedious</li>
<li>Takes a lot of space</li>
<li>Difficult to read quickly</li>
<li>Debugging more difficult because of tag pairing requirements</li>
<li>Indented code might not match nesting.</li>
<li>Confusing newline behaviour as they only occasionally break cells.</li></ul>
</td>
<td>
<ul><li>Unfamiliar syntax for experienced HTML editors</li>
<li>Rigid structure</li>
<li>Cannot be indented for clarity</li>
<li>HTML tag text may be easier to read than pipes, plus signs, dashes, etc.</li>
<li>Requires using <code>{{<a href="/wiki/Template:!" title="Template:!">!</a>}}</code> to pass a <code> | </code> character in a parameter.</li>
<li>Sensitive to newlines; see <a href="/wiki/Help:Newlines_and_spaces" title="Help:Newlines and spaces">Help:Newlines and spaces</a>.</li></ul>
</td></tr></tbody></table>, <table class="wikitable" style="margin: auto;">
<tbody><tr>
<td>1</td>
<td>2
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>3</td>
<td>4
</td></tr></tbody></table>, <table class="wikitable" style="text-align: center;">
<caption>Rotated column headers using <code>{{<a href="/wiki/Template:Vertical_header" title="Template:Vertical header">vertical header</a>}}</code>
</caption>
<tbody><tr>

<tbody><tr>
<th scope="col">Table element
</th>
<th scope="col">Wikitext
</th>
<th scope="col">Required
</th>
<th scope="col">Usage notes
</th></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table start
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">{|</kbd>
</td>
<td>Required
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table caption
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|+</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Only between table start and first table row.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table row
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|-</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Can be omitted before the first row.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table header cell
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">!</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Consecutive table header cells may be added on same line separated by double marks (<code>!!</code>); or start on new lines, each with its own single mark (<code>!</code>).
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table data cell
</th>
<td><span class="nowrap"><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|</kbd> or <kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">||</kbd></span>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Consecutive table data cells may be added on same line separated by double marks (<code>||</code>) or start on new lines, each with its own single mark (<code>|</code>). This mark is also used to separate <a href="/wiki/HTML_attribute" title="HTML attribute">HTML attributes</a> from cell and caption contents.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table end
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|}</kbd>
</td>
<td>Required
</td>
<td>

<th scope="row">Sample table
</th>
<td><div class="mw-highlight mw-highlight-lang-html mw-content-ltr" dir="ltr"><pre><span></span><span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">table</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>1<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>2<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>3<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>4<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">table</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
</pre></div>
</td>
<td><pre>{|
| 1 || 2
|-
| 3 || 4
|}</pre>
<div>
<table class="wikitable" style="margin: auto;">
<tbody><tr>
<td>1</td>
<td>2
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>3</td>
<td>4
</td></tr></tbody></table>
</div>
</td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top;">
<th scope="row">Pros
</th>
<td>
<ul><li>Can preview or debug with any XHTML editor</li>
<li>Can be indented for easier reading</li>
<li>Well-known</li>
<li>Insensitive to newlines</li>
<li>No characters like "|", which can collide with template and parser function syntax</li></ul>
</td>
<td>
<ul><li>Easy to write</li>
<li>Easy to read</li>
<li>Takes little space</li>
<li>Can be learned quickly</li></ul>
</td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top;">
<th scope="row">Cons
</th>
<td>
<ul><li>Tedious</li>
<li>Takes a lot of space</li>
<li>Difficult to read quickly</li>
<li>Debugging more difficult because of tag pairing requirements</li>
<li>Indented code might not match nesting.</li>
<li>Confusing newline behaviour as they only occasionally break cells.</li></ul>
</td>
<td>
<ul><li>Unfamiliar syntax for experienced HTML editors</li>
<li>Rigid structure</li>
<li>Cannot be indented for clarity</li>
<li>HTML tag text may be easier to read than pipes, plus signs, dashes, etc.</li>
<li>Requires using <code>{{<a href="/wiki/Template:!" title="Template:!">!</a>}}</code> to pass a <code> | </code> character in a parameter.</li>
<li>Sensitive to newlines; see <a href="/wiki/Help:Newlines_and_spaces" title="Help:Newlines and spaces">Help:Newlines and spaces</a>.</li></ul>
</td></tr></tbody></table>, <table class="wikitable" style="margin: auto;">
<tbody><tr>
<td>1</td>
<td>2
</td></tr>

<tbody><tr>
<th scope="col">Table element
</th>
<th scope="col">Wikitext
</th>
<th scope="col">Required
</th>
<th scope="col">Usage notes
</th></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table start
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">{|</kbd>
</td>
<td>Required
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table caption
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|+</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Only between table start and first table row.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table row
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|-</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Can be omitted before the first row.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table header cell
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">!</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Consecutive table header cells may be added on same line separated by double marks (<code>!!</code>); or start on new lines, each with its own single mark (<code>!</code>).
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table data cell
</th>
<td><span class="nowrap"><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|</kbd> or <kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">||</kbd></span>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Consecutive table data cells may be added on same line separated by double marks (<code>||</code>) or start on new lines, each with its own single mark (<code>|</code>). This mark is also used to separate <a href="/wiki/HTML_attribute" title="HTML attribute">HTML attributes</a> from cell and caption contents.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table end
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|}</kbd>
</td>
<td>Required
</td>
<td>

<th scope="row">Cell attribute
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;td style="font-size: 87%;"&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var>&lt;/td&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>| style="font-size: 87%;" | <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var></code>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Sample table
</th>
<td><div class="mw-highlight mw-highlight-lang-html mw-content-ltr" dir="ltr"><pre><span></span><span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">table</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>1<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>2<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>3<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>4<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">table</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
</pre></div>
</td>
<td><pre>{|
| 1 || 2
|-
| 3 || 4
|}</pre>
<div>
<table class="wikitable" style="margin: auto;">
<tbody><tr>
<td>1</td>
<td>2
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>3</td>
<td>4
</td></tr></tbody></table>
</div>
</td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top;">
<th scope="row">Pros
</th>
<td>
<ul><li>Can preview or debug with any XHTML editor</li>
<li>Can be indented for easier reading</li>
<li>Well-known</li>
<li>Insensitive to newlines</li>
<li>No characters like "|", which can collide with template and parser function syntax</li></ul>
</td>
<td>
<ul><li>Easy to write</li>
<li>Easy to read</li>
<li>Takes little space</li>
<li>Can be learned quickly</li></ul>
</td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top;">
<th scope="row">Cons
</th>
<td>
<ul><li>Tedious</li>
<li>Takes a lot of space</li>
<li>Difficult to read quickly</li>
<li>Debugging more difficult because of tag pairing requirements</li>
<li>Indented code might not match nesting.</li>
<li>Confusing newline behaviour as they only occasionally break cells.</li></ul>
</td>
<td>
<ul><li>Unfamiliar syntax for experienced HTML editors</li>
<li>Rigid structure</li>
<li>Cannot be indented for clarity</li>
<li>HTML tag text may be easier to read than pipes, plus signs, dashes, etc.</li>
<li>Requires using <code>{{<a href="/wiki/Template:!" title="Template:!">!</a>}}</code> to pass a <code> | </code> character in a parameter.</li>
<li>Sensitive to newlines; see <a href="/wiki/Help:Newlines_and_spaces" title="Help:Newlines and spaces">Help:Newlines and spaces</a>.</li></ul>
</td></tr></tbody></table>, <table class="wikitable" style="margin: auto;">
<tbody><tr>
<td>1</td>
<td>2
</td></tr>
<tr>

<tbody><tr>
<th scope="col">Table element
</th>
<th scope="col">Wikitext
</th>
<th scope="col">Required
</th>
<th scope="col">Usage notes
</th></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table start
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">{|</kbd>
</td>
<td>Required
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table caption
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|+</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Only between table start and first table row.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table row
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|-</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Can be omitted before the first row.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table header cell
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">!</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Consecutive table header cells may be added on same line separated by double marks (<code>!!</code>); or start on new lines, each with its own single mark (<code>!</code>).
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table data cell
</th>
<td><span class="nowrap"><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|</kbd> or <kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">||</kbd></span>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Consecutive table data cells may be added on same line separated by double marks (<code>||</code>) or start on new lines, each with its own single mark (<code>|</code>). This mark is also used to separate <a href="/wiki/HTML_attribute" title="HTML attribute">HTML attributes</a> from cell and caption contents.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table end
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|}</kbd>
</td>
<td>Required
</td>
<td>

<tbody><tr>
<td style="background-color: #eaecf0;">
</td>
<th scope="col">XHTML
</th>
<th scope="col">Wiki-pipe
</th></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;table&gt;...&lt;/table&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>{|<br/>...<br/>|}</code>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Caption
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;caption&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">caption</var>&lt;/caption&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>|+ <var style="padding-right: 1px;">caption</var></code>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Header cell
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;th scope="col"&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">column header</var>&lt;/th&gt;</code><br/>
<p><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;th scope="row"&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">row header</var>&lt;/th&gt;</code>
</p>
</td>
<td><code>! scope="col" | <var style="padding-right: 1px;">column header</var></code><br/>
<p><code>! scope="row" | <var style="padding-right: 1px;">row header</var></code>
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Row
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;tr&gt;...&lt;/tr&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>|-</code>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Data cell
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;td&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var>&lt;/td&gt;</code><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;td&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell2</var>&lt;/td&gt;</code><br/><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;td&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell3</var>&lt;/td&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>| <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var> || <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell2</var> || <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell3</var></code><br/>
<p>or<br/>
<code>| <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var></code><br/>
<code>| <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell2</var></code><br/>
<code>| <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell3</var></code>
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Cell attribute
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;td style="font-size: 87%;"&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var>&lt;/td&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>| style="font-size: 87%;" | <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var></code>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Sample table
</th>
<td><div class="mw-highlight mw-highlight-lang-html mw-content-ltr" dir="ltr"><pre><span></span><span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">table</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>1<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>2<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>3<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>4<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">table</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
</pre></div>
</td>
<td><pre>{|
| 1 || 2
|-
| 3 || 4
|}</pre>
<div>
<table class="wikitable" style="margin: auto;">
<tbody><tr>
<td>1</td>
<td>2
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>3</td>
<td>4
</td></tr></tbody></table>
</div>
</td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top;">
<th scope="row">Pros
</th>
<td>
<ul><li>Can preview or debug with any XHTML editor</li>
<li>Can be indented for easier reading</li>
<li>Well-known</li>
<li>Insensitive to newlines</li>
<li>No characters like "|", which can collide with template and parser function syntax</li></ul>
</td>
<td>
<ul><li>Easy to write</li>
<li>Easy to read</li>
<li>Takes little space</li>
<li>Can be learned quickly</li></ul>
</td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top;">
<th scope="row">Cons
</th>
<td>
<ul><li>Tedious</li>
<li>Takes a lot of space</li>
<li>Difficult to read quickly</li>
<li>Debugging more difficult because of tag pairing requirements</li>
<li>Indented code might not match nesting.</li>
<li>Confusing newline behaviour as they only occasionally break cells.</li></ul>
</td>
<td>
<ul><li>Unfamiliar syntax for experienced HTML editors</li>
<li>Rigid structure</li>
<li>Cannot be indented for clarity</li>
<li>HTML tag text may be easier to read than pipes, plus signs, dashes, etc.</li>
<li>Requires using <code>{{<a href="/wiki/Template:!" title="Template:!">!</a>}}</code> to pass a <code> | </code> character in a parameter.</li>
<li>Sensitive to newlines; see <a href="/wiki/Help:Newlines_and_spaces" title="Help:Newlines and spaces">Help:Newlines and spaces</a>.</li></ul>
</td></tr></tbody></table>, <table class="wikitable" style="margin: auto;">
<tbody><tr>
<td>1</td>
<td>2
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>3</td>
<td>4
</td></tr></tbody></table>, <table class="wikitable" style="text-align: center;">

<tbody><tr>
<th scope="col">Table element
</th>
<th scope="col">Wikitext
</th>
<th scope="col">Required
</th>
<th scope="col">Usage notes
</th></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table start
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">{|</kbd>
</td>
<td>Required
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table caption
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|+</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Only between table start and first table row.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table row
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|-</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Can be omitted before the first row.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table header cell
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">!</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Consecutive table header cells may be added on same line separated by double marks (<code>!!</code>); or start on new lines, each with its own single mark (<code>!</code>).
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table data cell
</th>
<td><span class="nowrap"><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|</kbd> or <kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">||</kbd></span>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Consecutive table data cells may be added on same line separated by double marks (<code>||</code>) or start on new lines, each with its own single mark (<code>|</code>). This mark is also used to separate <a href="/wiki/HTML_attribute" title="HTML attribute">HTML attributes</a> from cell and caption contents.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table end
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|}</kbd>
</td>
<td>Required
</td>
<td>
</td></tr></tbody></table>, <table class="plainlinks ombox ombox-style" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td class="mbox-image"><img alt="" data-file-height="48" data-file-width="48" decoding="async" height="40" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/f2/Edit-clear.svg/40px-Edit-clear.svg.png" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/f2/Edit-clear.svg/60px-Edit-clear.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/f2/Edit-clear.svg/80px-Edit-clear.svg.png 2x" width="40"/></td><td class="mbox-text">This help page <b>may require <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Cleanup" title="Wikipedia:Cleanup">cleanup</a> to meet Wikipedia's <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Manual_of_Style" title="Wikipedia:Manual of Style">quality standards</a></b>. <tbody><tr>
<td style="background-color: #eaecf0;">
</td>
<th scope="col">XHTML
</th>
<th scope="col">Wiki-pipe
</th></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;table&gt;...&lt;/table&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>{|<br/>...<br/>|}</code>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Caption
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;caption&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">caption</var>&lt;/caption&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>|+ <var style="padding-right: 1px;">caption</var></code>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Header cell
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;th scope="col"&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">column header</var>&lt;/th&gt;</code><br/>
<p><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;th scope="row"&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">row header</var>&lt;/th&gt;</code>
</p>
</td>
<td><code>! scope="col" | <var style="padding-right: 1px;">column header</var></code><br/>
<p><code>! scope="row" | <var style="padding-right: 1px;">row header</var></code>
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Row
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;tr&gt;...&lt;/tr&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>|-</code>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Data cell
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;td&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var>&lt;/td&gt;</code><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;td&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell2</var>&lt;/td&gt;</code><br/><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;td&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell3</var>&lt;/td&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>| <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var> || <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell2</var> || <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell3</var></code><br/>
<p>or<br/>
<code>| <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var></code><br/>
<code>| <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell2</var></code><br/>
<code>| <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell3</var></code>
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Cell attribute
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;td style="font-size: 87%;"&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var>&lt;/td&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>| style="font-size: 87%;" | <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var></code>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Sample table
</th>
<td><div class="mw-highlight mw-highlight-lang-html mw-content-ltr" dir="ltr"><pre><span></span><span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">table</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>1<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>2<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>3<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>4<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">table</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
</pre></div>
</td>
<td><pre>{|
| 1 || 2
|-
| 3 || 4
|}</pre>
<div>
<table class="wikitable" style="margin: auto;">
<tbody><tr>
<td>1</td>
<td>2
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>3</td>
<td>4
</td></tr></tbody></table>
</div>
</td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top;">
<th scope="row">Pros
</th>
<td>
<ul><li>Can preview or debug with any XHTML editor</li>
<li>Can be indented for easier reading</li>
<li>Well-known</li>
<li>Insensitive to newlines</li>
<li>No characters like "|", which can collide with template and parser function syntax</li></ul>
</td>
<td>
<ul><li>Easy to write</li>
<li>Easy to read</li>
<li>Takes little space</li>
<li>Can be learned quickly</li></ul>
</td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top;">
<th scope="row">Cons
</th>
<td>
<ul><li>Tedious</li>
<li>Takes a lot of space</li>
<li>Difficult to read quickly</li>
<li>Debugging more difficult because of tag pairing requirements</li>
<li>Indented code might not match nesting.</li>
<li>Confusing newline behaviour as they only occasionally break cells.</li></ul>
</td>
<td>
<ul><li>Unfamiliar syntax for experienced HTML editors</li>
<li>Rigid structure</li>
<li>Cannot be indented for clarity</li>
<li>HTML tag text may be easier to read than pipes, plus signs, dashes, etc.</li>
<li>Requires using <code>{{<a href="/wiki/Template:!" title="Template:!">!</a>}}</code> to pass a <code> | </code> character in a parameter.</li>
<li>Sensitive to newlines; see <a href="/wiki/Help:Newlines_and_spaces" title="Help:Newlines and spaces">Help:Newlines and spaces</a>.</li></ul>
</td></tr></tbody></table>, <table class="wikitable" style="margin: auto;">
<tbody><tr>

<td>2
</td></tr>

<tbody><tr>
<th scope="col">Table element
</th>
<th scope="col">Wikitext
</th>
<th scope="col">Required
</th>
<th scope="col">Usage notes
</th></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table start
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">{|</kbd>
</td>
<td>Required
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table caption
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|+</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Only between table start and first table row.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table row
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|-</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Can be omitted before the first row.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table header cell
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">!</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Consecutive table header cells may be added on same line separated by double marks (<code>!!</code>); or start on new lines, each with its own single mark (<code>!</code>).
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table data cell
</th>
<td><span class="nowrap"><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|</kbd> or <kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">||</kbd></span>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Consecutive table data cells may be added on same line separated by double marks (<code>||</code>) or start on new lines, each with its own single mark (<code>|</code>). This mark is also used to separate <a href="/wiki/HTML_attribute" title="HTML attribute">HTML attributes</a> from cell and caption contents.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table end
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|}</kbd>
</td>
<td>Required
</td>
<td>

<td>eu fugiat nulla</td>

<tbody><tr>
<td style="background-color: #eaecf0;">
</td>
<th scope="col">XHTML
</th>
<th scope="col">Wiki-pipe
</th></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;table&gt;...&lt;/table&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>{|<br/>...<br/>|}</code>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Caption
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;caption&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">caption</var>&lt;/caption&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>|+ <var style="padding-right: 1px;">caption</var></code>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Header cell
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;th scope="col"&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">column header</var>&lt;/th&gt;</code><br/>
<p><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;th scope="row"&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">row header</var>&lt;/th&gt;</code>
</p>
</td>
<td><code>! scope="col" | <var style="padding-right: 1px;">column header</var></code><br/>
<p><code>! scope="row" | <var style="padding-right: 1px;">row header</var></code>
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Row
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;tr&gt;...&lt;/tr&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>|-</code>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Data cell
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;td&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var>&lt;/td&gt;</code><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;td&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell2</var>&lt;/td&gt;</code><br/><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;td&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell3</var>&lt;/td&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>| <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var> || <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell2</var> || <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell3</var></code><br/>
<p>or<br/>
<code>| <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var></code><br/>
<code>| <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell2</var></code><br/>
<code>| <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell3</var></code>
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Cell attribute
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;td style="font-size: 87%;"&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var>&lt;/td&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>| style="font-size: 87%;" | <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var></code>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Sample table
</th>
<td><div class="mw-highlight mw-highlight-lang-html mw-content-ltr" dir="ltr"><pre><span></span><span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">table</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>1<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>2<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>3<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>4<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">table</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
</pre></div>
</td>
<td><pre>{|
| 1 || 2
|-
| 3 || 4
|}</pre>
<div>
<table class="wikitable" style="margin: auto;">
<tbody><tr>
<td>1</td>
<td>2
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>3</td>
<td>4
</td></tr></tbody></table>
</div>
</td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top;">
<th scope="row">Pros
</th>
<td>
<ul><li>Can preview or debug with any XHTML editor</li>
<li>Can be indented for easier reading</li>
<li>Well-known</li>
<li>Insensitive to newlines</li>
<li>No characters like "|", which can collide with template and parser function syntax</li></ul>
</td>
<td>
<ul><li>Easy to write</li>
<li>Easy to read</li>
<li>Takes little space</li>
<li>Can be learned quickly</li></ul>
</td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top;">
<th scope="row">Cons
</th>
<td>
<ul><li>Tedious</li>
<li>Takes a lot of space</li>
<li>Difficult to read quickly</li>
<li>Debugging more difficult because of tag pairing requirements</li>
<li>Indented code might not match nesting.</li>
<li>Confusing newline behaviour as they only occasionally break cells.</li></ul>
</td>
<td>
<ul><li>Unfamiliar syntax for experienced HTML editors</li>
<li>Rigid structure</li>
<li>Cannot be indented for clarity</li>
<li>HTML tag text may be easier to read than pipes, plus signs, dashes, etc.</li>
<li>Requires using <code>{{<a href="/wiki/Template:!" title="Template:!">!</a>}}</code> to pass a <code> | </code> character in a parameter.</li>
<li>Sensitive to newlines; see <a href="/wiki/Help:Newlines_and_spaces" title="Help:Newlines and spaces">Help:Newlines and spaces</a>.</li></ul>
</td></tr></tbody></table>, <table class="wikitable" style="margin: auto;">
<tbody><tr>
<td>1</td>
<td>2
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>3</td>
<td>4
</td></tr></tbody></table>, <table class="wikitable" style="text-align: center;">

<tbody><tr>
<th scope="col">Table element
</th>
<th scope="col">Wikitext
</th>
<th scope="col">Required
</th>
<th scope="col">Usage notes
</th></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table start
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">{|</kbd>
</td>
<td>Required
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table caption
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|+</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Only between table start and first table row.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table row
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|-</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Can be omitted before the first row.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table header cell
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">!</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Consecutive table header cells may be added on same line separated by double marks (<code>!!</code>); or start on new lines, each with its own single mark (<code>!</code>).
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table data cell
</th>
<td><span class="nowrap"><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|</kbd> or <kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">||</kbd></span>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Consecutive table data cells may be added on same line separated by double marks (<code>||</code>) or start on new lines, each with its own single mark (<code>|</code>). This mark is also used to separate <a href="/wiki/HTML_attribute" title="HTML attribute">HTML attributes</a> from cell and caption contents.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table end
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|}</kbd>
</td>
<td>Required
</td>
<td>

<tbody><tr>
<td style="background-color: #eaecf0;">
</td>
<th scope="col">XHTML
</th>
<th scope="col">Wiki-pipe
</th></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;table&gt;...&lt;/table&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>{|<br/>...<br/>|}</code>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Caption
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;caption&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">caption</var>&lt;/caption&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>|+ <var style="padding-right: 1px;">caption</var></code>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Header cell
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;th scope="col"&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">column header</var>&lt;/th&gt;</code><br/>
<p><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;th scope="row"&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">row header</var>&lt;/th&gt;</code>
</p>
</td>
<td><code>! scope="col" | <var style="padding-right: 1px;">column header</var></code><br/>
<p><code>! scope="row" | <var style="padding-right: 1px;">row header</var></code>
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Row
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;tr&gt;...&lt;/tr&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>|-</code>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Data cell
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;td&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var>&lt;/td&gt;</code><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;td&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell2</var>&lt;/td&gt;</code><br/><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;td&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell3</var>&lt;/td&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>| <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var> || <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell2</var> || <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell3</var></code><br/>
<p>or<br/>
<code>| <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var></code><br/>
<code>| <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell2</var></code><br/>
<code>| <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell3</var></code>
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Cell attribute
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;td style="font-size: 87%;"&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var>&lt;/td&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>| style="font-size: 87%;" | <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var></code>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Sample table
</th>
<td><div class="mw-highlight mw-highlight-lang-html mw-content-ltr" dir="ltr"><pre><span></span><span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">table</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>1<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>2<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>3<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>4<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">table</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
</pre></div>
</td>
<td><pre>{|
| 1 || 2
|-
| 3 || 4
|}</pre>
<div>

<td>2

<tr>
<td>3</td>
<td>4
</td></tr></tbody></table>
</div>
</td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top;">
<th scope="row">Pros
</th>
<td>
<ul><li>Can preview or debug with any XHTML editor</li>
<li>Can be indented for easier reading</li>
<li>Well-known</li>
<li>Insensitive to newlines</li>
<li>No characters like "|", which can collide with template and parser function syntax</li></ul>
</td>
<td>
<ul><li>Easy to write</li>
<li>Easy to read</li>
<li>Takes little space</li>
<li>Can be learned quickly</li></ul>
</td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top;">
<th scope="row">Cons
</th>
<td>
<ul><li>Tedious</li>
<li>Takes a lot of space</li>
<li>Difficult to read quickly</li>
<li>Debugging more difficult because of tag pairing requirements</li>
<li>Indented code might not match nesting.</li>
<li>Confusing newline behaviour as they only occasionally break cells.</li></ul>
</td>
<td>
<ul><li>Unfamiliar syntax for experienced HTML editors</li>
<li>Rigid structure</li>
<li>Cannot be indented for clarity</li>
<li>HTML tag text may be easier to read than pipes, plus signs, dashes, etc.</li>
<li>Requires using <code>{{<a href="/wiki/Template:!" title="Template:!">!</a>}}</code> to pass a <code> | </code> character in a parameter.</li>
<li>Sensitive to newlines; see <a href="/wiki/Help:Newlines_and_spaces" title="Help:Newlines and spaces">Help:Newlines and spaces</a>.</li></ul>
</td></tr></tbody></table>, <table class="wikitable" style="margin: auto;">
<tbody><tr>
<td>1</td>
<td>2
</td></tr>

<tbody><tr>
<th scope="col">Table element
</th>
<th scope="col">Wikitext
</th>
<th scope="col">Required
</th>
<th scope="col">Usage notes
</th></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table start
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">{|</kbd>
</td>
<td>Required
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table caption
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|+</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Only between table start and first table row.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table row
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|-</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Can be omitted before the first row.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table header cell
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">!</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Consecutive table header cells may be added on same line separated by double marks (<code>!!</code>); or start on new lines, each with its own single mark (<code>!</code>).
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table data cell
</th>
<td><span class="nowrap"><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|</kbd> or <kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">||</kbd></span>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Consecutive table data cells may be added on same line separated by double marks (<code>||</code>) or start on new lines, each with its own single mark (<code>|</code>). This mark is also used to separate <a href="/wiki/HTML_attribute" title="HTML attribute">HTML attributes</a> from cell and caption contents.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table end
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|}</kbd>
</td>
<td>Required
</td>
<td>

<tbody><tr>
<td style="background-color: #eaecf0;">
</td>
<th scope="col">XHTML
</th>
<th scope="col">Wiki-pipe
</th></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;table&gt;...&lt;/table&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>{|<br/>...<br/>|}</code>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Caption
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;caption&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">caption</var>&lt;/caption&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>|+ <var style="padding-right: 1px;">caption</var></code>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Header cell
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;th scope="col"&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">column header</var>&lt;/th&gt;</code><br/>
<p><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;th scope="row"&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">row header</var>&lt;/th&gt;</code>
</p>
</td>
<td><code>! scope="col" | <var style="padding-right: 1px;">column header</var></code><br/>
<p><code>! scope="row" | <var style="padding-right: 1px;">row header</var></code>
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Row
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;tr&gt;...&lt;/tr&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>|-</code>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Data cell
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;td&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var>&lt;/td&gt;</code><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;td&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell2</var>&lt;/td&gt;</code><br/><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;td&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell3</var>&lt;/td&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>| <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var> || <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell2</var> || <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell3</var></code><br/>
<p>or<br/>
<code>| <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var></code><br/>
<code>| <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell2</var></code><br/>
<code>| <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell3</var></code>
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Cell attribute
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;td style="font-size: 87%;"&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var>&lt;/td&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>| style="font-size: 87%;" | <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var></code>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Sample table
</th>
<td><div class="mw-highlight mw-highlight-lang-html mw-content-ltr" dir="ltr"><pre><span></span><span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">table</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>1<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>2<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>3<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>4<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">table</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
</pre></div>
</td>
<td><pre>{|
| 1 || 2
|-
| 3 || 4
|}</pre>
<div>
<table class="wikitable" style="margin: auto;">
<tbody><tr>
<td>1</td>
<td>2
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>3</td>
<td>4
</td></tr></tbody></table>
</div>
</td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top;">
<th scope="row">Pros
</th>
<td>
<ul><li>Can preview or debug with any XHTML editor</li>
<li>Can be indented for easier reading</li>
<li>Well-known</li>
<li>Insensitive to newlines</li>
<li>No characters like "|", which can collide with template and parser function syntax</li></ul>
</td>
<td>
<ul><li>Easy to write</li>
<li>Easy to read</li>
<li>Takes little space</li>
<li>Can be learned quickly</li></ul>
</td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top;">
<th scope="row">Cons
</th>
<td>
<ul><li>Tedious</li>
<li>Takes a lot of space</li>
<li>Difficult to read quickly</li>
<li>Debugging more difficult because of tag pairing requirements</li>
<li>Indented code might not match nesting.</li>
<li>Confusing newline behaviour as they only occasionally break cells.</li></ul>
</td>
<td>
<ul><li>Unfamiliar syntax for experienced HTML editors</li>
<li>Rigid structure</li>
<li>Cannot be indented for clarity</li>
<li>HTML tag text may be easier to read than pipes, plus signs, dashes, etc.</li>
<li>Requires using <code>{{<a href="/wiki/Template:!" title="Template:!">!</a>}}</code> to pass a <code> | </code> character in a parameter.</li>
<li>Sensitive to newlines; see <a href="/wiki/Help:Newlines_and_spaces" title="Help:Newlines and spaces">Help:Newlines and spaces</a>.</li></ul>
</td></tr></tbody></table>, <table class="wikitable" style="margin: auto;">
<tbody><tr>
<td>1</td>
<td>2
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>3</td>
<td>4
</td></tr></tbody></table>, <table class="wikitable" style="text-align: center;">
<caption>Rotated column headers using <code>{{<a href="/wiki/Template:Vertical_header" title="Template:Vertical header">vertical header</a>}}</code>
</caption>
<tbody><tr>

<tbody><tr>
<th scope="col">Table element
</th>
<th scope="col">Wikitext
</th>
<th scope="col">Required
</th>
<th scope="col">Usage notes
</th></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table start
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">{|</kbd>
</td>
<td>Required
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table caption
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|+</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Only between table start and first table row.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table row
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|-</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Can be omitted before the first row.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table header cell
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">!</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Consecutive table header cells may be added on same line separated by double marks (<code>!!</code>); or start on new lines, each with its own single mark (<code>!</code>).
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table data cell
</th>
<td><span class="nowrap"><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|</kbd> or <kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">||</kbd></span>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Consecutive table data cells may be added on same line separated by double marks (<code>||</code>) or start on new lines, each with its own single mark (<code>|</code>). This mark is also used to separate <a href="/wiki/HTML_attribute" title="HTML attribute">HTML attributes</a> from cell and caption contents.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table end
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|}</kbd>
</td>
<td>Required
</td>
<td>

<th scope="row">Sample table
</th>
<td><div class="mw-highlight mw-highlight-lang-html mw-content-ltr" dir="ltr"><pre><span></span><span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">table</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>1<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>2<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>3<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>4<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">table</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
</pre></div>
</td>
<td><pre>{|
| 1 || 2
|-
| 3 || 4
|}</pre>
<div>
<table class="wikitable" style="margin: auto;">
<tbody><tr>
<td>1</td>
<td>2
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>3</td>
<td>4
</td></tr></tbody></table>
</div>
</td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top;">
<th scope="row">Pros
</th>
<td>
<ul><li>Can preview or debug with any XHTML editor</li>
<li>Can be indented for easier reading</li>
<li>Well-known</li>
<li>Insensitive to newlines</li>
<li>No characters like "|", which can collide with template and parser function syntax</li></ul>
</td>
<td>
<ul><li>Easy to write</li>
<li>Easy to read</li>
<li>Takes little space</li>
<li>Can be learned quickly</li></ul>
</td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top;">
<th scope="row">Cons
</th>
<td>
<ul><li>Tedious</li>
<li>Takes a lot of space</li>
<li>Difficult to read quickly</li>
<li>Debugging more difficult because of tag pairing requirements</li>
<li>Indented code might not match nesting.</li>
<li>Confusing newline behaviour as they only occasionally break cells.</li></ul>
</td>
<td>
<ul><li>Unfamiliar syntax for experienced HTML editors</li>
<li>Rigid structure</li>
<li>Cannot be indented for clarity</li>
<li>HTML tag text may be easier to read than pipes, plus signs, dashes, etc.</li>
<li>Requires using <code>{{<a href="/wiki/Template:!" title="Template:!">!</a>}}</code> to pass a <code> | </code> character in a parameter.</li>
<li>Sensitive to newlines; see <a href="/wiki/Help:Newlines_and_spaces" title="Help:Newlines and spaces">Help:Newlines and spaces</a>.</li></ul>
</td></tr></tbody></table>, <table class="wikitable" style="margin: auto;">
<tbody><tr>
<td>1</td>
<td>2
</td></tr>

<tbody><tr>
<th scope="col">Table element
</th>
<th scope="col">Wikitext
</th>
<th scope="col">Required
</th>
<th scope="col">Usage notes
</th></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table start
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">{|</kbd>
</td>
<td>Required
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table caption
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|+</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Only between table start and first table row.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table row
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|-</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Can be omitted before the first row.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table header cell
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">!</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Consecutive table header cells may be added on same line separated by double marks (<code>!!</code>); or start on new lines, each with its own single mark (<code>!</code>).
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table data cell
</th>
<td><span class="nowrap"><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|</kbd> or <kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">||</kbd></span>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Consecutive table data cells may be added on same line separated by double marks (<code>||</code>) or start on new lines, each with its own single mark (<code>|</code>). This mark is also used to separate <a href="/wiki/HTML_attribute" title="HTML attribute">HTML attributes</a> from cell and caption contents.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table end
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|}</kbd>
</td>
<td>Required
</td>
<td>

<th scope="row">Cell attribute
</th>
<td><code class="nowrap" style="">&lt;td style="font-size: 87%;"&gt;<var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var>&lt;/td&gt;</code>
</td>
<td><code>| style="font-size: 87%;" | <var style="padding-right: 1px;">cell1</var></code>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Sample table
</th>
<td><div class="mw-highlight mw-highlight-lang-html mw-content-ltr" dir="ltr"><pre><span></span><span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">table</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>1<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>2<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>3<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
    <span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>4<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">td</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
  <span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">tr</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
<span class="p">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">table</span><span class="p">&gt;</span>
</pre></div>
</td>
<td><pre>{|
| 1 || 2
|-
| 3 || 4
|}</pre>
<div>
<table class="wikitable" style="margin: auto;">
<tbody><tr>
<td>1</td>
<td>2
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>3</td>
<td>4
</td></tr></tbody></table>
</div>
</td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top;">
<th scope="row">Pros
</th>
<td>
<ul><li>Can preview or debug with any XHTML editor</li>
<li>Can be indented for easier reading</li>
<li>Well-known</li>
<li>Insensitive to newlines</li>
<li>No characters like "|", which can collide with template and parser function syntax</li></ul>
</td>
<td>
<ul><li>Easy to write</li>
<li>Easy to read</li>
<li>Takes little space</li>
<li>Can be learned quickly</li></ul>
</td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align: top;">
<th scope="row">Cons
</th>
<td>
<ul><li>Tedious</li>
<li>Takes a lot of space</li>
<li>Difficult to read quickly</li>
<li>Debugging more difficult because of tag pairing requirements</li>
<li>Indented code might not match nesting.</li>
<li>Confusing newline behaviour as they only occasionally break cells.</li></ul>
</td>
<td>
<ul><li>Unfamiliar syntax for experienced HTML editors</li>
<li>Rigid structure</li>
<li>Cannot be indented for clarity</li>
<li>HTML tag text may be easier to read than pipes, plus signs, dashes, etc.</li>
<li>Requires using <code>{{<a href="/wiki/Template:!" title="Template:!">!</a>}}</code> to pass a <code> | </code> character in a parameter.</li>
<li>Sensitive to newlines; see <a href="/wiki/Help:Newlines_and_spaces" title="Help:Newlines and spaces">Help:Newlines and spaces</a>.</li></ul>
</td></tr></tbody></table>, <table class="wikitable" style="margin: auto;">
<tbody><tr>
<td>1</td>
<td>2
</td></tr>
<tr>

<tbody><tr>
<th scope="col">Table element
</th>
<th scope="col">Wikitext
</th>
<th scope="col">Required
</th>
<th scope="col">Usage notes
</th></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table start
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">{|</kbd>
</td>
<td>Required
</td>
<td>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table caption
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|+</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Only between table start and first table row.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table row
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|-</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Can be omitted before the first row.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table header cell
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">!</kbd>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Consecutive table header cells may be added on same line separated by double marks (<code>!!</code>); or start on new lines, each with its own single mark (<code>!</code>).
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table data cell
</th>
<td><span class="nowrap"><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|</kbd> or <kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">||</kbd></span>
</td>
<td>Optional
</td>
<td>Consecutive table data cells may be added on same line separated by double marks (<code>||</code>) or start on new lines, each with its own single mark (<code>|</code>). This mark is also used to separate <a href="/wiki/HTML_attribute" title="HTML attribute">HTML attributes</a> from cell and caption contents.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Table end
</th>
<td><kbd style="background:#EEEEEE; letter-spacing:0.05em; padding-left:0.25em; padding-right:0.2em;">|}</kbd>
</td>
<td>Required
</td>
<td>
